The paper discusses a matrix factorization algorithm and its applications, which are relevant to several sub-categories in computer science. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is a likely category as the paper proposes a new algorithm for matrix factorization. cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is also a possible category as the paper discusses the application of matrix factorization in clustering. cs.LG (Machine Learning) is another possible category as matrix factorization is a common technique in machine learning. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is a possible category as the paper discusses the scalability of the algorithm when applied to linked-data. cs.DB (Databases) is also a possible category as the paper discusses the efficiency of the algorithm when applied to a set of matrices representing a real multigraph.
